{"lemma":"حِنْطَةُ","slug":"حِنْطَةُ","root":"ح.ن.ط","root_slug":"ح-ن-ط","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-ن-ط","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n9312","n9316"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%90%D9%86%D9%92%D8%B7%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"spelt (Triticum spelta)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"wheat"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From a common Semitic root. Compare Hebrew חִטָּה (ḥiṭṭā́, “wheat”), Ugaritic 𐎈𐎉𐎚 (ḥṭt, “wheat”), Jewish Palestinian Aramaic and Jewish Babylonian Aramaic חִיטְּתָא (ḥiṭtəṯā, “wheat”) (absolute state: חִיטָּא (ḥiṭṭā)) / ܚܛܬܐ (ḥeṭtəṯā, “wheat”) (absolute state: ܚܛܐ (ḥeṭṭā)), Imperial Aramaic 𐡇𐡍𐡈𐡕𐡀 (ḥnṭtʾ, “wheat”) (absolute state: 𐡇𐡍𐡈𐡀 (ḥnṭʾ)), Palmyrene Aramaic 𐡧𐡨𐡠 (ḥṭʾ) (emphatic). Ge'ez ኅጠት (ḫəṭṭät), ሕጠት (ḥəṭṭät, “grain”), Soqotri ḥinṭeh (“wheat”), Mehri ḥeyṭ (“wheat”), Akkadian 𒊺 (/⁠uṭṭatu, eṭṭetu⁠/, “edible grains or kernels, especially barley or wheat”). With some likelihood ունդ (und), հունդ (hund, “edible seed, grain”) is related."},"ipa":["/ħin.tˤa/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n9312","headword_ar":"حنّطهُ","root":"HnT","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taHoniyTN","text_ar":"تَحْنِيطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA;) in the K, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HanaTahu","text_ar":"حَنَطَهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"; which is a mistake; (TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He prepared him"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a dead person [i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for burial"},{"kind":"text","text":"]) [and also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(grave-clothing)]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HanuwT","text_ar":"حَنُوط"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]; (S, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHnThu","text_ar":"احنطهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) And [hence,] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uHoniTa","text_ar":"اُحْنِطَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was prepared for burial with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HnwT","text_ar":"حنوط"},{"kind":"text","text":", is used to signify]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he died."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n9316","headword_ar":"حِنْطَةٌ","root":"HnT","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Wheat;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"grain of wheat;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bur~N","text_ar":"بُرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qamoHN","text_ar":"قَمْحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaEaAmN","text_ar":"طَعَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) of the first three of which words,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bur~N","text_ar":"بُرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the most chaste; (S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"br","text_ar":"بر"},{"kind":"text","text":";) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well-known grain called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bur~N","text_ar":"بُرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chewed, and applied as a poultice, it is good for the bite of a dog:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or, correctly,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is chewed thereof disperses humours; but for the bite of a dog, it is coarsely pounded, and put upon the bite;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as is said by the author of the “ Minháj: ” and one of its wellknown properties is this; that"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when it is put upon a piece of heated iron, and powdered, and ringworms"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qawaAbiY~","text_ar":"قَوَابِىّ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"are smeared with the moisture thereof, it removes them:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HinaTN","text_ar":"حِنَطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}